snippet.title: Homicide probe unidentified man's death
snippet.content: A man who died near a Melbourne train station after he was found with critical injuries is yet to be identified as homicide squad detectives launch an investigation. The man was found near a train station in West Footscray on Saturday night. Paramedics worked to revive him but he died at the scene, police say. The exact circumstances surrounding the death are yet to be determined. (C) AAP 2017
